responded: Now I can see the issue clearly. The problem is in the `xmlDictComputeFastKey` function. When `namelen` is 0, the code at line 451 tries to access `name[namelen - 1]` which becomes `name[-1]`, causing a heap buffer underflow (reading 1 byte before the allocated buffer).

Looking at the function:
1. Line 448: `value = *name;` - This accesses `name[0]` without checking if `namelen > 0`
2. Line 451: `value += name[namelen - 1];` - This accesses `name[namelen - 1]` when `namelen > 10`, but if `namelen` is 0, this becomes `name[-1]`

